---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Services — Don Krumpos">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1 class="page-header__title">Services</h1>
    <p class="page-header__subtitle">One practice. Three current shapes.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="services-intro">
    <p>
      I help organizations build digital experiences that feel like a place,
      not a product. The work below is three lenses on the same practice —
      a senior designer's eye, applied at three different scales of organization.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="service">
    <h2 class="service__title">Senior UX &amp; Design Systems</h2>
    <p>
      Twenty-five years across enterprise products, healthcare platforms, and
      data tools — in-house or as a contract design lead. The work shows up as
      research, information architecture, interaction design, and the design
      systems that hold a product together as it grows. The shape stays the
      same regardless of domain: understand the people who use the thing, find
      the structure the work actually wants, and build the components that let
      a team ship coherently against it.
    </p>
    <p class="service__outcome">
      <span class="service__outcome-label">A recent shape.</span>
      Contract design lead on NielsenIQ's Discover platform — built the design
      system from a 4px grid up, mapped the product information architecture,
      and shaped the guided flows analysts now use to navigate retail data.
      Related work for Optum's care-management tools and Patterson Dental's
      customer-facing site.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="service">
    <h2 class="service__title">Nonprofit Tech Strategy</h2>
    <p>
      Small organizations rarely need more software — they need the software
      they already have to behave like a system. I work with mission-driven
      teams on Salesforce, websites, photo and data archives, and the
      operational scaffolding that connects them. The work usually starts at
      the strategy layer — what are we actually trying to know about our work
      and our people? — and ends in the tooling, not the other way around.
      Built for budgets and staffing that have to outlast any one consultant.
    </p>
    <p class="service__outcome">
      <span class="service__outcome-label">A recent shape.</span>
      Designed and built an integrated strategic operating system for a small
      mission-driven nonprofit — Salesforce as the system of record, a
      public-facing website aligned to the program calendar, and an
      AI-assisted photo indexer that turned a decade of unsearchable event
      photography into institutional memory.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="service">
    <h2 class="service__title">Small Site Builds</h2>
    <p>
      Modern, owner-operated websites for artists, small organizations, and
      people who need a single clean signal on the open web. Built in Astro —
      fast, accessible, dependency-light, easy to maintain. The goal is a site
      you can keep without me: a calm structure, content you can edit in plain
      Markdown, and no surprise renewal fees from a platform you don't control.
    </p>
    <p class="service__outcome">
      <span class="service__outcome-label">A recent shape.</span>
      A freelance murals portfolio, a personal site at krumpos.org, and a
      regional arts site — each handed off to its owner running on
      infrastructure they understand.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="services-cta">
    <p>
      If any of this looks like a shape your work is asking for, the best next
      step is a short email. Tell me what you're working on, and I'll tell you
      whether I'm the right fit.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:don@yourdomain.com">don@yourdomain.com</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .services-intro {
    max-width: var(--max-width-prose);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .services-intro p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .service {
    max-width: var(--max-width-prose);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .service__title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .service p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .service__outcome {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .service__outcome-label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .services-cta {
    max-width: var(--max-width-prose);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .services-cta p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .services-cta a {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
